# ArrowERA CMS - Environment Configuration

## Required Variables

```env
# Application
NODE_ENV=development
APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
PORT=3000

# Database (PostgreSQL)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/arrowera_cms

# Authentication (generate with: openssl rand -hex 32)
AUTH_SECRET=your-secret-key-at-least-32-characters-long

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=info
```

## Optional Variables

```env
# Database Pooling
DATABASE_POOL_SIZE=10
DATABASE_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT=5000

# Redis (for production sessions and caching)
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# Security
CSRF_SECRET=your-csrf-secret-at-least-32-characters
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=60000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=100
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:4000

# Storage (S3-compatible)
STORAGE_PROVIDER=s3
S3_BUCKET=your-bucket-name
S3_REGION=us-east-1
S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-access-key
S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-secret-key
S3_ENDPOINT=https://s3.amazonaws.com
```

## Environment-Specific Examples

### Development (.env.development)

```env
NODE_ENV=development
APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
PORT=3000
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/arrowera_dev
AUTH_SECRET=dev-secret-change-in-production-min-32-chars
LOG_LEVEL=debug
```

### Staging (.env.staging)

```env
NODE_ENV=staging
APP_URL=https://staging.arrowera.com
PORT=3000
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@staging-db:5432/arrowera
AUTH_SECRET=staging-secret-from-secrets-manager
REDIS_URL=redis://staging-redis:6379
LOG_LEVEL=info
CORS_ORIGINS=https://staging.arrowera.com
```

### Production (.env.production)

```env
NODE_ENV=production
APP_URL=https://arrowera.com
PORT=3000
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@prod-db:5432/arrowera
AUTH_SECRET=production-secret-from-secrets-manager
REDIS_URL=redis://prod-redis:6379
LOG_LEVEL=warn
CORS_ORIGINS=https://arrowera.com,https://www.arrowera.com
RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=50
```

## Validation

The configuration system validates all required variables at startup. If validation fails, the application will exit with a descriptive error message.

## Secret Management

For production deployments:

1. **Docker**: Use Docker secrets or environment files
2. **Kubernetes**: Use Secrets resources
3. **Cloud**: Use AWS Secrets Manager, GCP Secret Manager, or Azure Key Vault
4. **VPS**: Use encrypted environment files with restricted permissions

Never commit `.env` files to version control!
